<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Currently the prepare() method in Zend_Db_Adapter_Pdo_Abstract returns an object of type PDOStatement.  When methods of this object throw exceptions, they throw PDOException.</p>

<p>This makes the interface inconsistent with usage of non-PDO adapters, that return objects extending Zend_Db_Statement_Interface, and throwing exceptions deriving from Zend_Db_Statement_Exception.</p>

<p>Please create  proxy class to wrap PDOStatement into a class in the proper hierarchy.  Catch all PDOExceptions and re-throw them as Zend_Db_Statement_Exception.</p>

